<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-462-233  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 462 233.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Sept 24 1990 n319 pS10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What managers think about industry issues. (TCA Membership Surveysupplement) (includes related article on what benefits matter tomanagers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Semilof, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Most corporate organizations are now aware of the strategicimportance of their network and communications systems.andP;  A recentpoll of members of the Telecommunications Association (TCA),conducted by Communications Week, shows that over 74 percent ofmanagers agree that communications and network systems are nowviewed as strategic assets.andP;  However, 25 percent believe thattheir management does not view communications and network systemsas a strategic priority.andP;  The poll shows that the margin ofsupport for the systems in the transportation industry was higherdue to support from their executives.andP;  In a close second were TCAmembers in the financial industry and in utility companies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SurveyStrategic PlanningNetworksManagement-EDP RelationsTrade and Professional AssociationsCommunications IndustryManagement of EDP.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Managements' views on communications and networks strategicassets. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>